+ Review Attention Levels

[[tabview]]
[[tab Review Attention Levels]]
This is an overview over the Review Attention Level of all pages in this wiki.

The Review Attention Level indicates the priority and the grade of necessity to review and correct that article:

* o = Quite good, not much to do, just a last check.
* oo = Needs minor attention. Spelling and grammar are mostly correct.
* ooo = Needs major attention. Some sentences and expressions may need to be rephrased. Spelling and grammar may need correction.
* oooo = Emergency! Partially rewrite may be necessary, while MTFs secure the premises.

Everybody who reviews a translation removes one "o'', __though the last level may only be removed by members of the Review Team!__ This means that all new translations are at least level "o''. If the last level is removed, it is replaced with "_o''. This tag is normally invisible and is used by automated lists.

Whenever translators post their work in the wiki, they estimate the Review Attention Level of their translation, with a minimum of "o''. Staff and fluent English-speakers may change the Level if they think it doesn't fit.

